## Next.js + shadcn/ui Commands Cheat Sheet

Follow these commands to create a new Next.js app and add shadcn/ui components. See full guide in `nextjs-shadcn-setup.mdc` or official docs: `https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/installation/next`.

### Create app (non-interactive, recommended)
```bash
pnpm create next-app@latest my-app \
  --ts \
  --tailwind \
  --eslint \
  --app \
  --use-pnpm \
  --no-git \
  --import-alias "@/*"
```

### Enter project
```bash
cd my-app
```

### Initialize shadcn/ui
```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest init
```
- Choose "Next.js" (or "Monorepo" if applicable)

### Add components
```bash
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button
# or multiple at once
pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add button input label card
```

### Run dev server
```bash
pnpm dev
```

### Notes
- For existing Next.js apps, start from "Initialize shadcn/ui".
- Re-run `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <component>` whenever you need new components.